FRAMEWORK SPECIFICATION REVIEW

Review the current Master List Framework Specification against the current production script.

The objective is to verify that the governing framework documentation accurately represents the implemented framework.

The current production script is the implementation source of truth.

Review:

• Overall framework architecture
• Processing workflow
• Module organization
• Dashboard architecture
• Template architecture
• Configuration architecture
• Sheet definitions
• Sheet lifecycle
• Mapping definitions
• Column definitions
• Header definitions
• Data ownership
• Processing ownership
• Synchronization rules
• Data flow
• Validation workflow
• Quality Assurance workflow
• Error handling strategy
• Logging strategy
• Template governance
• Dashboard governance
• Protected standards
• Naming conventions
• Configuration standards

Verify that the specification accurately documents:

• Entry points
• Workflow order
• Processing sequence
• Business rules
• Data transformations
• Synchronization behavior
• Dashboard behavior
• Template behavior
• Report generation
• Validation logic
• Framework governance decisions
• Module responsibilities
• Public interfaces

Identify:

• Missing documentation
• Outdated specifications
• Deprecated architecture
• Removed features still documented
• New features not documented
• Incorrect workflow descriptions
• Incorrect mapping definitions
• Incorrect sheet definitions
• Incorrect processing descriptions
• Specification inconsistencies
• Documentation conflicts
• Governance conflicts

Recommend updates only where the specification no longer reflects the implemented framework.

Do not recommend architectural redesign unless a true architectural defect exists.

Do not recommend changes solely for stylistic consistency.

Preserve all approved business rules and framework governance.

The goal is to ensure that the Framework Specification accurately documents the current production framework and serves as the governing technical reference for future development.
